What is Java?

High-level, object-oriented, platform-independent programming language.

â€œWrite Once, Run Anywhereâ€ â†’ JVM executes bytecode on any OS.

Core Java Concepts

JVM (Java Virtual Machine) â†’ executes bytecode.

JRE (Java Runtime Environment) â†’ JVM + libraries for running apps.

JDK (Java Development Kit) â†’ JRE + compiler (javac) for development.

Bytecode â†’ compiled .class files understood by JVM.

OOP Principles (important for microservices design)

Encapsulation

Inheritance

Polymorphism

Abstraction

Basic Commands

javac HelloWorld.java    # compile
java HelloWorld          # run
java -version            # check version


âœ… Must-know to understand how Java apps run in containers/Kubernetes.

ğŸ”¹ 2. Medium-Level Concepts (Practical DevOps Usage)

Build Tools

Maven â†’ uses pom.xml, dependency + build management.

Gradle â†’ faster, uses Groovy/Kotlin DSL.

Ant (legacy).

Packaging & Deployment

.jar (Java Archive) â†’ libraries or standalone apps.

.war (Web Archive) â†’ deploy on servlet container (Tomcat, JBoss).

.ear (Enterprise Archive) â†’ legacy enterprise apps.

Spring Boot (Most Common in DevOps)

Embedded Tomcat â†’ no need for external server.

REST APIs â†’ microservices architecture.

Profiles (dev, test, prod).

Externalized configs (application.yml, Config Server, Consul, Vault).

Logging

Log4j, Logback, SLF4J.

Logs â†’ shipped to ELK/EFK stack.

Testing

JUnit, Mockito.

Important for CI/CD pipelines.

Environment Variables

Pass configs/secrets into apps via -Dproperty=value or env vars.

âœ… This is where DevOps interacts daily with Java apps.

ğŸ”¹ 3. Advanced Concepts (FAANG-Level)

JVM Internals

Class Loader â†’ loads classes.

JIT Compiler (Just-In-Time) â†’ optimizes bytecode at runtime.

Garbage Collector (GC) â†’ frees unused memory. Types:

Serial GC

Parallel GC

G1 GC (common in production).

JVM Tuning

Heap size: -Xmx512m -Xms256m.

GC tuning for performance.

Thread dumps, heap dumps (troubleshooting).

Monitoring & Profiling

JConsole, JVisualVM â†’ monitor heap, threads.

Prometheus JMX Exporter â†’ expose JVM metrics.

Grafana Dashboards â†’ visualize JVM performance.

Java in Containers

Slim JDK/JRE base images (AdoptOpenJDK, Eclipse Temurin).

Multi-stage Docker builds â†’ reduce image size.

Use jlink to create minimal runtime images.

Security

Avoid hardcoding secrets (use Vault, Kubernetes secrets).

HTTPS/TLS config for Spring Boot apps.

JVM Security Manager (deprecated in Java 17+).

âœ… These topics are favorite FAANG interview questions for DevOps engineers.

